From c47be5130c1d71af169e393fd3be7f35af5c4ba2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 10:00:11 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Improve performance, player features, and upload UX

- Share a single cached track fetch (React Query) across the homepage
  and search bar instead of two independent network requests, with
  proper error surfacing via toast and a skeleton loading state.
- Invalidate the tracks cache after a successful upload so new tracks
  appear immediately without a manual refresh.
- Player: add volume control + mute, shuffle, repeat (off/all/one),
  and keyboard shortcuts (space, arrow keys, N/P). Playback state
  (track, position, volume, shuffle, repeat) now persists across
  page reloads via localStorage.
- Upload: validate file size client-side (100MB audio / 8MB cover),
  show a cover art preview, and show real upload progress bars via
  a direct XHR call to the Storage REST endpoint (the supabase-js
  client doesn't expose progress events).
- Clean up remaining  types across the codebase in favor of
  proper types / instanceof Error checks.
